  "title": "Hadoop MapReduce Cluster Architecture",
  "description": "The Hadoop MapReduce cluster architecture comprises Java-based components that ensure seamless job execution and management. The `ClusterMetrics.java` class tracks cluster performance, while `ContextFactory.java` creates MapReduce Context Objects, facilitating interaction between tasks. `CryptoUtils.java` ensures data security via encryption, and `CustomJobEndNotifier.java` allows for tailored job completion notifications.\n\n`MRJobConfig.java` and `MapContext.java` configure and provide context to the Mapper, respectively. `MarkableIterator.java` and `MarkableIteratorInterface.java` support data navigation, while `OutputCommitter.java` and `OutputFormat.java` manage task output commit and specifications. `QueueAclsInfo.java` and `QueueInfo.java` handle job queue ACLs and information, and `RecordReader.java` defines the abstract RecordReader class for input data reading.\n\nThis architecture demonstrates high scalability, maintainability, and reliability, leveraging Java as the primary technology. It employs patterns such as factory (ContextFactory.java) and observer (CustomJobEndNotifier.java) to ensure efficient job execution and management in the MapReduce framework.",
